fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
The universal property of the product P =   \prod _{j\in  J} X_j with projections P \xrightarrow {\pi _k} X_k is that, for any
  object Z equipped with morphisms Z\xrightarrow {\tau _k} X_k, there exists a unique
  morphism Z\to  P making the following diagrams commute:




    \usepackage{tikz, tikz-cd, mathtools, amssymb}
  \usetikzlibrary{shapes.geometric}
  \usetikzlibrary{calc}
  \usetikzlibrary{matrix}
  \usetikzlibrary{decorations.markings}

